.TH IFCONFIG 8
.SH NAME
ifconfig \- configure a network interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ifconfig
.RI [ ip ]
.RB [ netmask
.IR mask ]
.RB [ gateway
.IR gw ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ifconfig
displays or sets the IP address, netmask, and gateway for the Ethernet
interface via the ktcp netconf protocol.  The ktcp daemon must be running.
.PP
Without arguments,
.B ifconfig
displays the current network configuration, including the hardware (MAC)
address, IP address, netmask, and gateway.
.PP
With arguments, it updates the specified parameters.  All changes take effect
immediately in ktcp; no reboot is required.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I ip
Set the local IP address.  Example: \fB10.0.2.15\fR.
.TP
.B netmask
.I mask
Set the network mask.  Example: \fB255.255.255.0\fR.
.TP
.B gateway
.I gw
Set the default gateway IP address.  Example: \fB10.0.2.2\fR.
.SH EXAMPLE
.PP
.nf
ifconfig 10.0.2.15 netmask 255.255.255.0 gateway 10.0.2.2
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR ping (8),
.BR ktcp (8).
